<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1375">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/909.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests in Mexico</hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department encloses a copy of a
                            despatch [of November 5] from the Vice Consul at Guadalajara, Mexico,
                            setting forth the arbitrary manner in which mining interests are being
                            treated by the present de facto government in Mexico.</p>
                        <p>You are instructed to bring the statements contained therein to the
                            attention of the appropriate authorities, in connection with previous
                            representations, and earnestly to continue your efforts for a material
                            modification of the decree imposing increased taxes upon mining
                            properties.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>